    "id": 1063,
    "question": "Problem: Suppose the price of sugar fluctuates within a range of 5% to 15% increase from its current price of Rs. 10 per kg. For each percentage increase from 5% to 15% with increments of 1%, calculate the reduction in sugar consumption a person would have to make to maintain their expenditure on sugar. Consider that the person currently consumes 'x' kg of sugar at Rs. 10 per kg.\n\nSolution: \n\nWe will first calculate the new prices for each percentage increase and then calculate the reduction in sugar consumption accordingly.\n\nLet's represent the percentage increase as 'p'.\n\n1. New price per kg for each percentage increase: \n      New Price = Current Price * (1 + p/100)\n\n2. Calculation of reduced sugar consumption to maintain the expenditure on sugar:\n      x kg * Rs 10 = Reduced Consumption (in kg) * New Price (in Rs)\n      \n      Reduced Consumption (in kg) = (x kg * Rs 10) / New Price (in Rs)\n\nNow, for each percentage increase, repeat the steps 1 and 2 and calculate the Reduced Consumption (in kg).\n\n### Answer:",
    "options": [
      "Option A",
      "Option B",
      "Option C",
      "Option D"
    ],
    "correct": 0,
    "explanation": "Let's calculate the new price and reduced consumption for each percentage increase from 5% to 15%.\n\nFor p = 5%:\n1. New Price = Rs 10 * (1 + 5/100) = Rs 10 * 1.05 = Rs 10.50\n2. Reduced Consumption = (x * Rs 10) / Rs 10.50 = x / 1.05\n\nFor p = 6%:\n1. New Price = Rs 10 * (1 + 6/100) = Rs 10 * 1.06 = Rs 10.60\n2. Reduced Consumption = (x * Rs 10) / Rs 10.60 = x / 1.06\n\nFor p = 7%:\n1. New Price = Rs 10 * (1 + 7/100) = Rs 10 * 1.07 = Rs 10.70\n2. Reduced Consumption = (x * Rs 10) / Rs 10.70 = x / 1.07\n\nFor p = 8%:\n1. New Price = Rs 10 * (1 + 8/100) = Rs 10 * 1.08 = Rs 10.80\n2. Reduced Consumption = (x * Rs 10) / Rs 10.80 = x / 1.08\n\nFor p = 9%:\n1. New Price = Rs 10 * (1 + 9/100) = Rs 10 * 1.09 = Rs 10.90\n2. Reduced Consumption = (x * Rs 10) / Rs 10.90 = x / 1.09\n\nFor p = 10%:\n1. New Price = Rs 10 * (1 + 10/100) = Rs 10 * 1.10 = Rs 11.00\n2. Reduced Consumption = (x * Rs 10) / Rs 11.00 = x / 1.10\n\nFor p = 11%:\n1. New Price = Rs 10 * (1 + 11/100) = Rs 10 * 1.11 = Rs 11.10\n2. Reduced Consumption = (x * Rs 10) / Rs 11.10 = x / 1.11\n\nFor p = 12%:\n1. New Price = Rs 10 * (1 + 12/100) = Rs 10 * 1.12 = Rs 11.20\n2. Reduced Consumption = (x * Rs 10) / Rs 11.20 = x / 1.12\n\nFor p = 13%:\n1. New Price = Rs 10 * (1 + 13/100) = Rs 10 * 1.13 = Rs 11.30\n2. Reduced Consumption = (x * Rs 10) / Rs 11.30 = x / 1.13\n\nFor p = 14%:\n1. New Price = Rs 10 * (1 + 14/100) = Rs 10 * 1.14 = Rs 11.40\n2. Reduced Consumption = (x * Rs 10) / Rs 11.40 = x / 1.14\n\nFor p = 15%:\n1. New Price = Rs 10 * (1 + 15/100) = Rs 10 * 1.15 = Rs 11.50\n2. Reduced Consumption = (x * Rs 10) / Rs 11.50 = x / 1.15\n\nSo, for each percentage increase from 5% to 15%, the reduced consumption can be calculated by dividing the original consumption 'x' by the factor (1 + p/100).",
