    "correct": 0,
    "explanation": "Let's denote the distances traveled by the asteroids as D1, D2, D3, D4, D5, D6, and D7, and their speeds as S1, S2, S3, S4, S5, S6, and S7.\n\nFrom the information given:\n\n1. \\( D1 = 2D2 \\) and \\( S1 = S2 + 1500 \\)\n2. \\( D3 = 3D2 \\), \\( S3 = S2 + 4500 \\), and \\( t3 = t1 + 3 \\)\n3. \\( D4 = 4D2 \\), \\( S4 = S2 \\), and \\( t4 = 2t1 \\)\n4. \\( D5 = 40000 \\), \\( D6 = 20000 \\), \\( S5 = S6 \\), and \\( t5 = t6 = t1 \\)\n5. \\( D7 = 10D2 \\), \\( S7 = 2S3 \\), and \\( t7 = t1 \\)\n\nWe know that distance (D) is the product of speed (S) and time (t), so we can write:\n\n\\( D1 = S1 * t1 \\)\n\\( D2 = S2 * t2 \\)\n\\( D3 = S3 * t3 \\)\n\\( D4 = S4 * t4 \\)\n\\( D5 = S5 * t5 \\)\n\\( D6 = S6 * t6 \\)\n\\( D7 = S7 * t7 \\)\n\nUsing the relationships given:\n\n1. \\( D1 = 2D2 \\) and \\( S1 = S2 + 1500 \\)\n   \\( D1 = (S2 + 1500) * t1 \\)\n   \\( 2D2 = (S2 + 1500) * t1 \\)\n   \\( 2S2 * t2 = (S2 + 1500) * t1 \\)\n\n2. \\( D3 = 3D2 \\) and \\( S3 = S2 + 4500 \\)\n   \\( D3 = (S2 + 4500) * t3 \\)\n   \\( 3D2 = (S2 + 4500) * (t1 + 3) \\)\n   \\( 3S2 * t2 = (S2 + 4500) * (t1 + 3) \\)\n\n3. \\( D4 = 4D2 \\) and \\( S4 = S2 \\)\n   \\( D4 = S2 * t4 \\)\n   \\( 4D2 = S2 * 2t1 \\)\n   \\( 4S2 * t2 = S2 * 2t1 \\)\n\n4. \\( D5 = 40000 \\) and \\( D6 = 20000 \\)\n   \\( S5 * t1 = 40000 \\)\n   \\( S6 * t1 = 20000 \\)\n   Since \\( S5 = S6 \\), we can say \\( t1 = 2t6 \\)\n\n5. \\( D7 = 10D2 \\) and \\( S7 = 2S3 \\)\n   \\( D7 = 2S3 * t7 \\)\n   \\( 10D2 = 2(S2 + 4500) * t1 \\)\n   \\( 10S2 * t2 = 2(S2 + 4500) * t1 \\)\n\nNow, we have a system of equations that we can solve. However, we need more information to find the exact values of the speeds and times. We can only solve this system if we have the values for either the speeds or the times of at least some of the asteroids. Without additional information, we can't determine the exact distances and durations.",
