    "id": 1066,
    "question": "John, an international businessman, made the following purchases and sales:\n\nHe purchased a grinder for Rs. 15,000 in India and a mobile phone for $100 in the USA. He also bought a refrigerator for £200 in the UK and a television for €300 in Germany.\n\nUpon his return, he sold the grinder in India at a loss of 4%, the mobile phone in the USA at a profit of 10%, the refrigerator in the UK at a profit of 8%, and the television in Germany at a loss of 6%.\n\nThe exchange rates at the time of his business venture were as follows: $1 = Rs. 75 and £1 = Rs. 101, €1 = Rs. 90.\n\nAdditionally, consider that John has to pay the following taxes on his profits: 5% in India, 7% in the USA, 6% in the UK, and 9% in Germany.\n\nCalculate John's overall profit or loss from these ventures considering different currencies, exchange rates, buying/selling prices, and tax percentages.\n\n### Answer:",
    "options": [
      "Option A",
      "Option B",
      "Option C",
      "Option D"
    ],
    "correct": 0,
    "explanation": "Let's calculate the profit or loss for each item individually, including the exchange rates and taxes.\n\n**Grinder (India):**\n- Purchase price: Rs. 15,000\n- Selling price at a loss of 4%: Rs. 15,000 - (4/100 * 15,000) = Rs. 15,000 - Rs. 600 = Rs. 14,400\n- Loss on grinder: Rs. 600\n- Tax on profit: Not applicable as there is a loss.\n\n**Mobile Phone (USA):**\n- Purchase price in $: $100\n- Purchase price in Rs.: $100 * Rs. 75 = Rs. 7,500\n- Selling price at a profit of 10%: $100 + (10/100 * $100) = $100 + $10 = $110\n- Selling price in Rs.: $110 * Rs. 75 = Rs. 8,250\n- Profit on mobile phone: Rs. 8,250 - Rs. 7,500 = Rs. 750\n- Tax on profit at 7%: 7/100 * Rs. 750 = Rs. 52.50\n- Profit after tax: Rs. 750 - Rs. 52.50 = Rs. 697.50\n\n**Refrigerator (UK):**\n- Purchase price in £: £200\n- Purchase price in Rs.: £200 * Rs. 101 = Rs. 20,200\n- Selling price at a profit of 8%: £200 + (8/100 * £200) = £200 + £16 = £216\n- Selling price in Rs.: £216 * Rs. 101 = Rs. 21,816\n- Profit on refrigerator: Rs. 21,816 - Rs. 20,200 = Rs. 1,616\n- Tax on profit at 6%: 6/100 * Rs. 1,616 = Rs. 96.96\n- Profit after tax: Rs. 1,616 - Rs. 96.96 = Rs. 1,519.04\n\n**Television (Germany):**\n- Purchase price in €: €300\n- Purchase price in Rs.: €300 * Rs. 90 = Rs. 27,000\n- Selling price at a loss of 6%: €300 - (6/100 * €300) = €300 - €18 = €282\n- Selling price in Rs.: €282 * Rs. 90 = Rs. 25,380\n- Loss on television: Rs. 27,000 - Rs. 25,380 = Rs. 1,620\n- Tax on profit: Not applicable as there is a loss.\n\nNow, let's calculate the overall profit or loss by summing up the individual profits and losses:\n\nOverall profit or loss = (Profit after tax on mobile phone + Profit after tax on refrigerator) - (Loss on grinder + Loss on television)\n\nOverall profit or loss = (Rs. 697.50 + Rs. 1,519.04) - (Rs. 600 + Rs. 1,620)\n\nOverall profit or loss = Rs. 2,216.54 - Rs. 2,220\n\nOverall profit or loss = Rs. -3.46\n\nJohn has an overall loss of Rs. 3.46 from his international business ventures.",
