    "id": 1068,
    "question": "Cary starts working at Game Stop for $10/hour. In the first year, she works 40 hours a week for 50 weeks, with 2 weeks of vacation. After this year, she gets a 20% raise. Additionally, she earns a performance bonus of $500 at the end of the year. \n\nIn the second year, her base pay is cut to 75% of what it used to be due to the company's profits decreasing, but she is now working an average of 50 hours per week, where hours beyond 40 are paid at 1.5 times the normal rate. She takes only 1 week of vacation in the second year. Moreover, she incurs a $300 penalty for underperformance in the second year.\n\nIn the third year, she receives another 10% raise of her base pay, almost back to her original starting wage, and her hours go back to 40 hours a week with 2 weeks of vacation. Also, she earns a performance bonus of $1,000 at the end of the third year.\n\nThroughout these three years, the income tax rates change: in the first year, it is 20%; in the second year, 22%; and in the third year, it is 18%. Calculate Cary's total net earnings, after taxes and accounting for bonuses and penalties, over these three years.\n\n### Answer:",
    "options": [
      "Option A",
      "Option B",
      "Option C",
      "Option D"
    ],
    "correct": 0,
    "explanation": "Let's calculate Cary's earnings year by year.\n\n**Year 1:**\n- Base hourly wage: $10\n- Hours worked per week: 40\n- Weeks worked: 50 (2 weeks of vacation)\n- Yearly hours: 40 hours/week * 50 weeks = 2000 hours\n- Gross earnings: 2000 hours * $10/hour = $20,000\n- Performance bonus: $500\n- Total gross earnings: $20,000 + $500 = $20,500\n- Tax rate: 20%\n- Taxes paid: $20,500 * 20% = $4,100\n- Net earnings: $20,500 - $4,100 = $16,400\n\n**Year 2:**\n- Base hourly wage after 20% raise: $10 * 120% = $12\n- Base hourly wage after 25% cut: $12 * 75% = $9\n- Regular hours worked per week: 40\n- Overtime hours worked per week: 10\n- Weeks worked: 51 (1 week of vacation)\n- Yearly regular hours: 40 hours/week * 51 weeks = 2040 hours\n- Yearly overtime hours: 10 hours/week * 51 weeks = 510 hours\n- Overtime pay rate: $9 * 1.5 = $13.5\n- Gross earnings from regular hours: 2040 hours * $9/hour = $18,360\n- Gross earnings from overtime hours: 510 hours * $13.5/hour = $6,885\n- Total gross earnings: $18,360 + $6,885 = $25,245\n- Underperformance penalty: $300\n- Total gross earnings after penalty: $25,245 - $300 = $24,945\n- Tax rate: 22%\n- Taxes paid: $24,945 * 22% = $5,487.90\n- Net earnings: $24,945 - $5,487.90 = $19,457.10\n\n**Year 3:**\n- Base hourly wage after 10% raise: $9 * 110% = $9.9\n- Hours worked per week: 40\n- Weeks worked: 50 (2 weeks of vacation)\n- Yearly hours: 40 hours/week * 50 weeks = 2000 hours\n- Gross earnings: 2000 hours * $9.9/hour = $19,800\n- Performance bonus: $1,000\n- Total gross earnings: $19,800 + $1,000 = $20,800\n- Tax rate: 18%\n- Taxes paid: $20,800 * 18% = $3,744\n- Net earnings: $20,800 - $3,744 = $17,056\n\n**Total net earnings over three years:**\n- Year 1: $16,400\n- Year 2: $19,457.10\n- Year 3: $17,056\n- Total: $16,400 + $19,457.10 + $17,056 = $52,913.10\n\nCary's total net earnings over the three years are $52,913.10.",
