    "explanation": "First, let's calculate the marked price for each item by adding the respective percentage to the cost price.\n\nFor item A:\nMarked Price (MP) = Cost Price (CP) + (Percentage Markup * CP)\nMP_A = Rs. 540 + (15% of Rs. 540)\nMP_A = Rs. 540 + (0.15 * Rs. 540)\nMP_A = Rs. 540 + Rs. 81\nMP_A = Rs. 621\n\nFor item B:\nMP_B = Rs. 450 + (20% of Rs. 450)\nMP_B = Rs. 450 + (0.20 * Rs. 450)\nMP_B = Rs. 450 + Rs. 90\nMP_B = Rs. 540\n\nFor item C:\nMP_C = Rs. 600 + (10% of Rs. 600)\nMP_C = Rs. 600 + (0.10 * Rs. 600)\nMP_C = Rs. 600 + Rs. 60\nMP_C = Rs. 660\n\nNow, let's calculate the discount percentage for each item using the final selling price and the marked price.\n\nFor item A:\nDiscount Amount (DA) = MP - Final Selling Price (FSP)\nDA_A = Rs. 621 - Rs. 460\nDA_A = Rs. 161\n\nDiscount Percentage (DP) = (DA / MP) * 100\nDP_A = (Rs. 161 / Rs. 621) * 100\nDP_A = 0.2592 * 100\nDP_A = 25.92%\n\nFor item B:\nDA_B = Rs. 540 - Rs. 410\nDA_B = Rs. 130\n\nDP_B = (Rs. 130 / Rs. 540) * 100\nDP_B = 0.2407 * 100\nDP_B = 24.07%\n\nFor item C:\nDA_C = Rs. 660 - Rs. 570\nDA_C = Rs. 90\n\nDP_C = (Rs. 90 / Rs. 660) * 100\nDP_C = 0.1364 * 100\nDP_C = 13.64%\n\nNow we have the discount percentages for each item:\nx = 25.92%\ny = 24.07%\nz = 13.64%\n\nTo calculate the overall discount percentage for the total selling price of all three items, we need to find the total cost price, total marked price, and total selling price.\n\nTotal Cost Price (TCP) = CP_A + CP_B + CP_C\nTCP = Rs. 540 + Rs. 450 + Rs. 600\nTCP = Rs. 1590\n\nTotal Marked Price (TMP) = MP_A + MP_B + MP_C\nTMP = Rs. 621 + Rs. 540 + Rs. 660\nTMP = Rs. 1821\n\nTotal Selling Price (TSP) = FSP_A + FSP_B + FSP_C\nTSP = Rs. 460 + Rs. 410 + Rs. 570\nTSP = Rs. 1440\n\nTotal Discount Amount (TDA) = TMP - TSP\nTDA = Rs. 1821 - Rs. 1440\nTDA = Rs. 381\n\nOverall Discount Percentage (ODP) = (TDA / TMP) * 100\nODP = (Rs. 381 / Rs. 1821) * 100\nODP = 0.2092 * 100\nODP = 20.92%\n\nSo, the overall discount percentage for the total selling price of all three items is 20.92%.",
