    "id": 1070,
    "question": "Calculate the combined amount after 5 years for the following investments, with the given interest rates per annum compounded annually:\n\nInvestment A: Principal amount Rs. 12000 with interest rates: 4% for the first year, 5% for the second year, 3% for the third year, 6% for the fourth year, and 4% for the fifth year.\n\nInvestment B: Principal amount Rs. 15000 with interest rates: 5% for the first year, 4% for the second year, 7% for the third year, 2% for the fourth year, and 6% for the fifth year.\n\nInvestment C: Principal amount Rs. 10000 with interest rates: 6% for the first year, 4% for the second year, 5% for the third year, 3% for the fourth year, and 7% for the fifth year.\n\n### Answer:",
