    "explanation": "To calculate the combined amount for each investment after 5 years with varying interest rates, we will apply the formula for compound interest for each year separately:\n\nA = P(1 + r/n)^(nt)\n\nWhere:\nA = the future value of the investment/loan, including interest\nP = the principal investment amount (the initial deposit or loan amount)\nr = the annual interest rate (decimal)\nn = the number of times that interest is compounded per year\nt = the number of years the money is invested or borrowed for\n\nSince the interest is compounded annually, n = 1 for all investments.\n\nLet's calculate the future value for each investment:\n\nInvestment A:\nYear 1: A1 = 12000 * (1 + 0.04) = 12000 * 1.04 = Rs. 12480\nYear 2: A2 = A1 * (1 + 0.05) = 12480 * 1.05 = Rs. 13104\nYear 3: A3 = A2 * (1 + 0.03) = 13104 * 1.03 = Rs. 13497.12\nYear 4: A4 = A3 * (1 + 0.06) = 13497.12 * 1.06 = Rs. 14306.94\nYear 5: A5 = A4 * (1 + 0.04) = 14306.94 * 1.04 = Rs. 14879.22\n\nInvestment B:\nYear 1: B1 = 15000 * (1 + 0.05) = 15000 * 1.05 = Rs. 15750\nYear 2: B2 = B1 * (1 + 0.04) = 15750 * 1.04 = Rs. 16380\nYear 3: B3 = B2 * (1 + 0.07) = 16380 * 1.07 = Rs. 17526.6\nYear 4: B4 = B3 * (1 + 0.02) = 17526.6 * 1.02 = Rs. 17877.13\nYear 5: B5 = B4 * (1 + 0.06) = 17877.13 * 1.06 = Rs. 18949.36\n\nInvestment C:\nYear 1: C1 = 10000 * (1 + 0.06) = 10000 * 1.06 = Rs. 10600\nYear 2: C2 = C1 * (1 + 0.04) = 10600 * 1.04 = Rs. 11024\nYear 3: C3 = C2 * (1 + 0.05) = 11024 * 1.05 = Rs. 11575.2\nYear 4: C4 = C3 * (1 + 0.03) = 11575.2 * 1.03 = Rs. 11922.66\nYear 5: C5 = C4 * (1 + 0.07) = 11922.66 * 1.07 = Rs. 12756.65\n\nNow, let's add the future values of all three investments to get the combined amount after 5 years:\n\nCombined amount = A5 + B5 + C5\nCombined amount = Rs. 14879.22 + Rs. 18949.36 + Rs. 12756.65\nCombined amount = Rs. 46585.23\n\nTherefore, the combined amount after 5 years for the three investments is Rs. 46585.23.",
