    "id": 1071,
    "question": "Tom opened a shop investing Rs. 30,000. Jose joined him 2 months later, investing Rs. 45,000. Four months after Tom started the business, Maria also joined them, investing Rs. 60,000. Over the course of a year, each month's profit or loss varied. The monthly net amounts were as follows:\n\n1. Rs. 5,000 profit\n2. Rs. 2,000 loss\n3. Rs. 7,000 profit\n4. Rs. 1,000 profit\n5. Rs. 3,000 loss\n6. Rs. 10,000 profit\n7. Rs. 500 profit\n8. Rs. 4,000 profit\n9. Rs. 2,500 loss\n10. Rs. 6,000 profit\n11. Rs. 8,000 profit\n12. Rs. 1,000 loss\n\nWith these varying profits and losses, what will be Jose's share of the overall profit at the end of the year?\n\n### Answer:",
