    "id": 1074,
    "question": "John purchased items from different countries with varying tax rates and discounts. He bought a grinder for $150 with a 10% sales tax, a mobile phone for €100 with a 5% discount and 15% VAT, a laptop for £200 with an 8% tax, and a camera for ¥12,000 with a 12% discount and 5% consumption tax. He sold the items at the following profits and losses: grinder at a 4% loss, mobile phone at a 10% profit, laptop at an 8% loss, and camera at a 15% profit. Calculate the overall profit or loss John made from all these transactions, assuming the following conversion rates: 1 USD = 75 INR, 1 EUR = 80 INR, 1 GBP = 100 INR, 1 JPY = 0.7 INR.\n\n### Answer:",
    "options": [
      "Option A",
      "Option B",
      "Option C",
      "Option D"
    ],
    "correct": 0,
    "explanation": "Let's calculate the cost price (CP) for each item including taxes and discounts, and then the selling price (SP) based on the profit or loss percentage. Finally, we'll convert everything to INR to calculate the overall profit or loss.\n\n1. Grinder:\n- Cost price (CP) with tax: $150 + 10% of $150 = $150 + $15 = $165\n- Selling price (SP) with loss: $165 - 4% of $165 = $165 - $6.60 = $158.40\n- CP in INR: $165 * 75 INR = 12375 INR\n- SP in INR: $158.40 * 75 INR = 11880 INR\n\n2. Mobile Phone:\n- Discounted price: €100 - 5% of €100 = €100 - €5 = €95\n- Cost price (CP) with VAT: €95 + 15% of €95 = €95 + €14.25 = €109.25\n- Selling price (SP) with profit: €109.25 + 10% of €109.25 = €109.25 + €10.925 = €120.175\n- CP in INR: €109.25 * 80 INR = 8740 INR\n- SP in INR: €120.175 * 80 INR = 9614 INR\n\n3. Laptop:\n- Cost price (CP) with tax: £200 + 8% of £200 = £200 + £16 = £216\n- Selling price (SP) with loss: £216 - 8% of £216 = £216 - £17.28 = £198.72\n- CP in INR: £216 * 100 INR = 21600 INR\n- SP in INR: £198.72 * 100 INR = 19872 INR\n\n4. Camera:\n- Discounted price: ¥12,000 - 12% of ¥12,000 = ¥12,000 - ¥1440 = ¥10,560\n- Cost price (CP) with tax: ¥10,560 + 5% of ¥10,560 = ¥10,560 + ¥528 = ¥11,088\n- Selling price (SP) with profit: ¥11,088 + 15% of ¥11,088 = ¥11,088 + ¥1663.2 = ¥12,751.2\n- CP in INR: ¥11,088 * 0.7 INR = 7761.6 INR\n- SP in INR: ¥12,751.2 * 0.7 INR = 8925.84 INR\n\nNow, let's calculate the overall profit or loss:\n\nTotal CP in INR = 12375 + 8740 + 21600 + 7761.6 = 50476.6 INR\nTotal SP in INR = 11880 + 9614 + 19872 + 8925.84 = 50291.84 INR\n\nOverall Profit or Loss = Total SP - Total CP\nOverall Profit or Loss = 50291.84 INR - 50476.6 INR\nOverall Profit or Loss = -184.76 INR\n\nJohn made an overall loss of 184.76 INR from all these transactions.",
