    "explanation": "Let's denote the original cost prices of articles A, B, and C as \\( C_A \\), \\( C_B \\), and \\( C_C \\) respectively. The original selling prices (SP) of A, B, and C can be denoted as \\( SP_A \\), \\( SP_B \\), and \\( SP_C \\) respectively.\n\nGiven the profit percentages for A, B, and C are 25%, 20%, and 30% respectively, we can write the following equations for the original selling prices:\n\n\\[ SP_A = C_A + 0.25C_A = 1.25C_A \\]\n\\[ SP_B = C_B + 0.20C_B = 1.20C_B \\]\n\\[ SP_C = C_C + 0.30C_C = 1.30C_C \\]\n\nNow, if the shopkeeper had purchased article A at 15% less, the new cost price of A would be \\( 0.85C_A \\). Similarly, the new cost prices for B and C would be \\( 0.80C_B \\) and \\( 0.75C_C \\) respectively.\n\nThe new selling prices after reducing Rs. 5.10, Rs. 8.25, and Rs. 12.75 would be \\( SP_A - 5.10 \\), \\( SP_B - 8.25 \\), and \\( SP_C - 12.75 \\) respectively.\n\nThe new profit percentages are increased by 5% for each article, so they become 30%, 25%, and 35% respectively. We can write the equations for the new selling prices as:\n\n\\[ SP_A - 5.10 = 1.30(0.85C_A) \\]\n\\[ SP_B - 8.25 = 1.25(0.80C_B) \\]\n\\[ SP_C - 12.75 = 1.35(0.75C_C) \\]\n\nSubstituting the original selling prices in terms of the original cost prices, we get:\n\n\\[ 1.25C_A - 5.10 = 1.30(0.85C_A) \\]\n\\[ 1.20C_B - 8.25 = 1.25(0.80C_B) \\]\n\\[ 1.30C_C - 12.75 = 1.35(0.75C_C) \\]\n\nNow, we can solve these equations to find the original cost prices of A, B, and C.\n\nFor article A:\n\\[ 1.25C_A - 5.10 = 1.105C_A \\]\n\\[ 1.25C_A - 1.105C_A = 5.10 \\]\n\\[ 0.145C_A = 5.10 \\]\n\\[ C_A = \\frac{5.10}{0.145} \\]\n\\[ C_A = 35.17 \\]\n\nFor article B:\n\\[ 1.20C_B - 8.25 = 1.00C_B \\]\n\\[ 1.20C_B - 1.00C_B = 8.25 \\]\n\\[ 0.20C_B = 8.25 \\]\n\\[ C_B = \\frac{8.25}{0.20} \\]\n\\[ C_B = 41.25 \\]\n\nFor article C:\n\\[ 1.30C_C - 12.75 = 1.0125C_C \\]\n\\[ 1.30C_C - 1.0125C_C = 12.75 \\]\n\\[ 0.2875C_C = 12.75 \\]\n\\[ C_C = \\frac{12.75}{0.2875} \\]\n\\[ C_C = 44.35 \\]\n\nTherefore, the original cost prices of articles A, B, and C are Rs. 35.17, Rs. 41.25, and Rs. 44.35 respectively.",
