    "question": "Mac loves the shape of quarters and is willing to trade money for them, even if he loses value. Over the course of a week, he tells his brother that he will trade him different coins each day. Here is the breakdown of the coins he trades daily:\n\nDay 1: Mac will trade 6 Canadian dimes and 2 Canadian pennies for a quarter.\nDay 2: Mac will trade 10 Mexican centavos and 5 Cuban centavos for a quarter.\nDay 3: Mac will trade 4 US dimes and 1 Euro cent for a quarter.\nDay 4: Mac will trade 7 UK pence and 5 Canadian nickels for a quarter.\nDay 5: Mac will trade 3 US half-dollar coins and 2 Brazilian centavos for a quarter.\nDay 6: Mac will trade 12 Australian cents and 3 Indian paise for a quarter.\nDay 7: Mac will trade 8 Mexican pesos and 6 Japanese yen for a quarter.\n\nGiven the following exchange rates:\n1 Canadian dime = 0.075 USD\n1 Canadian penny = 0.0075 USD\n1 Mexican centavo = 0.0045 USD\n1 Cuban centavo = 0.0036 USD\n1 Euro cent = 0.011 USD\n1 UK pence = 0.013 USD\n1 Canadian nickel = 0.038 USD\n1 US half-dollar coin = 0.5 USD\n1 Brazilian centavo = 0.0019 USD\n1 Australian cent = 0.0072 USD\n1 Indian paisa = 0.0013 USD\n1 Mexican peso = 0.045 USD\n1 Japanese yen = 0.0089 USD\n\nCalculate the amount Mac lost over the week by giving quarters in exchange for the different coins each day.\n\n### Answer:",
