    "explanation": "To calculate the amount Mac lost over the week, we need to first determine the value of the coins he traded each day in USD and then compare it to the value of a quarter, which is 0.25 USD.\n\nDay 1: \n6 Canadian dimes = 6 * 0.075 USD = 0.45 USD\n2 Canadian pennies = 2 * 0.0075 USD = 0.015 USD\nTotal value traded = 0.45 USD + 0.015 USD = 0.465 USD\nLoss for Day 1 = 0.465 USD - 0.25 USD = 0.215 USD\n\nDay 2:\n10 Mexican centavos = 10 * 0.0045 USD = 0.045 USD\n5 Cuban centavos = 5 * 0.0036 USD = 0.018 USD\nTotal value traded = 0.045 USD + 0.018 USD = 0.063 USD\nLoss for Day 2 = 0.25 USD - 0.063 USD = 0.187 USD\n\nDay 3:\n4 US dimes = 4 * 0.10 USD = 0.40 USD\n1 Euro cent = 1 * 0.011 USD = 0.011 USD\nTotal value traded = 0.40 USD + 0.011 USD = 0.411 USD\nLoss for Day 3 = 0.411 USD - 0.25 USD = 0.161 USD\n\nDay 4:\n7 UK pence = 7 * 0.013 USD = 0.091 USD\n5 Canadian nickels = 5 * 0.038 USD = 0.19 USD\nTotal value traded = 0.091 USD + 0.19 USD = 0.281 USD\nLoss for Day 4 = 0.281 USD - 0.25 USD = 0.031 USD\n\nDay 5:\n3 US half-dollar coins = 3 * 0.5 USD = 1.5 USD\n2 Brazilian centavos = 2 * 0.0019 USD = 0.0038 USD\nTotal value traded = 1.5 USD + 0.0038 USD = 1.5038 USD\nLoss for Day 5 = 1.5038 USD - 0.25 USD = 1.2538 USD\n\nDay 6:\n12 Australian cents = 12 * 0.0072 USD = 0.0864 USD\n3 Indian paise = 3 * 0.0013 USD = 0.0039 USD\nTotal value traded = 0.0864 USD + 0.0039 USD = 0.0903 USD\nLoss for Day 6 = 0.25 USD - 0.0903 USD = 0.1597 USD\n\nDay 7:\n8 Mexican pesos = 8 * 0.045 USD = 0.36 USD\n6 Japanese yen = 6 * 0.0089 USD = 0.0534 USD\nTotal value traded = 0.36 USD + 0.0534 USD = 0.4134 USD\nLoss for Day 7 = 0.4134 USD - 0.25 USD = 0.1634 USD\n\nTotal loss over the week:\n0.215 USD (Day 1) + 0.187 USD (Day 2) + 0.161 USD (Day 3) + 0.031 USD (Day 4) + 1.2538 USD (Day 5) + 0.1597 USD (Day 6) + 0.1634 USD (Day 7) = 2.1619 USD\n\nMac lost a total of 2.1619 USD over the course of the week by trading quarters for different coins each day.",
