    "question": "Jonathan's daily calorie intake varies as follows:\n\n- On Mondays, he consumes 2500 calories, including 1000 calories from proteins, 1200 calories from carbohydrates, and 300 calories from fats. His exercise routine on Mondays consists of an hour of weightlifting, burning 400 calories, and an hour of high-intensity interval training, burning 600 calories.\n- On Tuesdays, he consumes 2600 calories, including 1100 calories from proteins, 1300 calories from carbohydrates, and 200 calories from fats. His exercise routine on Tuesdays consists of 3 hours of brisk walking, burning 200 calories per hour for a total of 600 calories, and an hour of swimming, burning 600 calories.\n- On Wednesdays, he consumes 2400 calories, including 1000 calories from proteins, 1200 calories from carbohydrates, and 200 calories from fats. His exercise routine on Wednesdays consists of an hour of cycling, burning 800 calories, followed by an hour of basketball, burning 500 calories.\n- On Thursdays, he consumes 2700 calories, including 1200 calories from proteins, 1300 calories from carbohydrates, and 200 calories from fats. His exercise routine on Thursdays consists of 2 hours of running, burning 800 calories per hour for a total of 1600 calories.\n- On Fridays, he consumes 2300 calories, including 900 calories from proteins, 1100 calories from carbohydrates, and 300 calories from fats. His exercise routine on Fridays consists of one hour of yoga, burning 300 calories, followed by 90 minutes of soccer, burning 700 calories.\n- On Saturdays, he consumes 3500 calories, including 1300 calories from proteins, 1600 calories from carbohydrates, and 600 calories from fats. On this day, he does not perform any exercise and maintains a relaxed schedule.\n- On Sundays, he consumes 2400 calories, including 1000 calories from proteins, 1200 calories from carbohydrates, and 200 calories from fats. His exercise routine on Sundays consists of 2 hours of hiking, burning 600 calories per hour for a total of 1200 calories.\n\nWhat is Jonathan's weekly caloric deficit, taking into consideration his varying daily calorie intake and exercise routines?\n\n### Answer:",
