    "question": "A company employs three workers, A, B, and C, who complete various types of surveys: basic surveys, lifestyle surveys, and technology surveys, with each type having different payment rates and some involving commission-based payments.\n\nWorker A is paid a regular rate of Rs. 30 for completing a basic survey, with the rate being 20% higher for lifestyle surveys and 50% higher for technology surveys. Worker B is paid Rs. 25 for basic surveys, with the rate being 25% higher for lifestyle surveys and 45% higher for technology surveys. Worker C is paid a regular rate of Rs. 35 for basic surveys, with the rate being 15% higher for lifestyle surveys and 60% higher for technology surveys.\n\nAll workers receive a 5% commission on the total cost of the technology surveys they complete in a week, in addition to their regular wage. After their weekly earnings have been calculated, they pay taxes at the following rates: Worker A pays 15% income tax, Worker B pays 18% income tax, and Worker C pays 20% income tax.\n\nIn a given week, Worker A completes 80 basic surveys, 50 lifestyle surveys, and 35 technology surveys; Worker B completes 90 basic surveys, 45 lifestyle surveys, and 40 technology surveys; and Worker C completes 70 basic surveys, 40 lifestyle surveys, and 60 technology surveys. Calculate their weekly earnings and post-tax income, taking into consideration any additional deductions such as health insurance (Worker A: Rs. 200, Worker B: Rs. 250, and Worker C: Rs. 300).\n\n### Answer:",
