    "explanation": "Let's calculate the weekly earnings for each worker before taxes and deductions.\n\n**Worker A:**\n- Basic surveys: 80 surveys * Rs. 30/survey = Rs. 2400\n- Lifestyle surveys: 50 surveys * Rs. 30/survey * 120% = Rs. 1800\n- Technology surveys: 35 surveys * Rs. 30/survey * 150% = Rs. 1575\n- Commission for technology surveys: Rs. 1575 * 5% = Rs. 78.75\n\nTotal earnings for Worker A before taxes = Rs. 2400 + Rs. 1800 + Rs. 1575 + Rs. 78.75 = Rs. 5853.75\n\n**Worker B:**\n- Basic surveys: 90 surveys * Rs. 25/survey = Rs. 2250\n- Lifestyle surveys: 45 surveys * Rs. 25/survey * 125% = Rs. 1406.25\n- Technology surveys: 40 surveys * Rs. 25/survey * 145% = Rs. 1450\n- Commission for technology surveys: Rs. 1450 * 5% = Rs. 72.50\n\nTotal earnings for Worker B before taxes = Rs. 2250 + Rs. 1406.25 + Rs. 1450 + Rs. 72.50 = Rs. 5178.75\n\n**Worker C:**\n- Basic surveys: 70 surveys * Rs. 35/survey = Rs. 2450\n- Lifestyle surveys: 40 surveys * Rs. 35/survey * 115% = Rs. 1610\n- Technology surveys: 60 surveys * Rs. 35/survey * 160% = Rs. 3360\n- Commission for technology surveys: Rs. 3360 * 5% = Rs. 168\n\nTotal earnings for Worker C before taxes = Rs. 2450 + Rs. 1610 + Rs. 3360 + Rs. 168 = Rs. 7588\n\nNow, let's calculate the post-tax income for each worker after deducting income tax and health insurance.\n\n**Worker A:**\n- Income tax: Rs. 5853.75 * 15% = Rs. 878.06\n- Health insurance: Rs. 200\n- Post-tax income: Rs. 5853.75 - Rs. 878.06 - Rs. 200 = Rs. 4775.69\n\n**Worker B:**\n- Income tax: Rs. 5178.75 * 18% = Rs. 932.18\n- Health insurance: Rs. 250\n- Post-tax income: Rs. 5178.75 - Rs. 932.18 - Rs. 250 = Rs. 3996.57\n\n**Worker C:**\n- Income tax: Rs. 7588 * 20% = Rs. 1517.60\n- Health insurance: Rs. 300\n- Post-tax income: Rs. 7588 - Rs. 1517.60 - Rs. 300 = Rs. 5770.40\n\nSo, the post-tax income for each worker is:\n- Worker A: Rs. 4775.69\n- Worker B: Rs. 3996.57\n- Worker C: Rs. 5770.40",
