    "question": "Haily decided to treat herself to a full day of pampering at the salon. She wants to get her nails done, have a haircut, get a facial cleaning, a foot spa, and a massage. She is on a tight budget and therefore wants to carefully analyze and choose the most affordable option. \n\nShe contacted four salons to get their prices: Gustran Salon, Barbara's Shop, The Fancy Salon, and the Luxury Spa. The pricing for the services are as follows: \n\nAt Gustran Salon, the prices are as follows: haircut $45, facial $22, nails $30, foot spa $15, and massage $50. They also have a special package where if you avail of all services, you get a 20% discount.\n\nAt Barbara's Shop, the charges are: nails $40, haircut $30, facial $28, foot spa $18, and massage $45. Barbara also offers a loyalty scheme where every third service on the same day costs half the price.\n\nThe Fancy Salon's list includes the haircut for $34, facial cleaning for $30, nails for $20, foot spa for $25, and massage for $60. They have a special offer where if you spend more than $130, you save $15.\n\nLastly, at the Luxury Spa, each service cost 10% more than the average price of that service in the other three salons, but they offer a flat $20 discount if you're a new customer.\n\nHaily needs to work out which salon will be the cheapest option for her.\n\n\n### Answer:",
