    "id": 1209,
    "question": "Two containers hold different solutions. Container 1 has 500 milliliters of solution A, which is X% salt by weight and Y% sugar by weight. Container 2 has 750 milliliters of solution B, which is Y% salt by weight and Z% sugar by weight. \n\n150 milliliters of solution A is removed from Container 1 and replaced with an equal volume of solution B from Container 2. The resulting solution in Container 1 has 450 milliliters of solution and is 15% salt and 12% sugar by weight. Afterward, 200 milliliters of solution B is removed from Container 2 and replaced with an equal volume of solution A from Container 1. The resulting solution in Container 2 has 600 milliliters of solution and is 18% salt and 10% sugar by weight. \n\nFind the unknown values X, Y, and Z representing the salt and sugar percentages in solutions A and B.\n\n### Answer:",
