    "question": "In the year 2000, the town of Youngsville had a population of 684 people with 55% being male and 45% being female. The town's population was divided into three age groups: 30% were under the age of 18, 50% were between 18 and 59 years old, and the remaining 20% were 60 years and older.\n\nIn the year 2010, the town experienced a growth spurt with a population increase of 25%, and the ratios of gender remained the same. However, the age groups shifted to 25% under 18, 60% between 18 and 59 years old, and 15% of 60 years and older. The town was booming with opportunities.\n\nUnfortunately, by the year 2015, 40% of the population moved away due to an economic downturn. But before they left, the age groups slightly changed, with 20% being under 18 years old, 65% between 18 and 59 years old, and 15% at 60 years and older.\n\nCalculate the current population of Youngsville in the year 2015, along with the number of males and females and the headcount in each age group.\n\n### Answer:",
