    "id": 1223,
    "question": "On a particular week, two libraries - Library A and Library B - recorded their check-outs and returns. At Library A, they checked out 320 books distributed into the following categories: 100 Fiction, 80 Fantasy, 40 Horror, 60 Romance, and 40 Non-fiction. In the same week, they had 420 returned books in the same categories in the following quantities: 120 Fiction, 100 Fantasy, 60 Horror, 80 Romance, and 60 Non-fiction. \n\nAt Library B, they checked out 450 books distributed into the following categories: 150 Fiction, 75 Fantasy, 60 Horror, 90 Romance, and 75 Non-fiction. In the same week, they had 500 returned books in the same categories in the following quantities: 170 Fiction, 110 Fantasy, 70 Horror, 100 Romance, and 50 Non-fiction.\n\nAnswer the following questions:\n\n1. Calculate the ratio of Fiction to Non-fiction books checked out in each library.\n2. Find the ratio of checked-out Fantasy, Horror, and Romance books combined to Fiction and Non-fiction books combined at each library.\n3. Calculate the percentage of checked-out books in each category at both libraries.\n4. Determine the difference in the overall ratio of checked-out Fiction and Non-fiction books between Library A and Library B.\n5. Using the return data, compare the ratio of returned Fantasy, Horror, and Romance books combined to returned Fiction and Non-fiction books combined in both libraries.\n\n### Answer:",
