    "explanation": "1. Ratio of Fiction to Non-fiction books checked out in each library:\n- Library A: 100 Fiction / 40 Non-fiction = 100:40 = 5:2\n- Library B: 150 Fiction / 75 Non-fiction = 150:75 = 2:1\n\n2. Ratio of checked-out Fantasy, Horror, and Romance books combined to Fiction and Non-fiction books combined at each library:\n- Library A: (80 Fantasy + 40 Horror + 60 Romance) / (100 Fiction + 40 Non-fiction) = (180) / (140) = 180:140 = 9:7\n- Library B: (75 Fantasy + 60 Horror + 90 Romance) / (150 Fiction + 75 Non-fiction) = (225) / (225) = 225:225 = 1:1\n\n3. Percentage of checked-out books in each category at both libraries:\n- Library A:\n  - Fiction: (100 / 320) * 100 = 31.25%\n  - Fantasy: (80 / 320) * 100 = 25%\n  - Horror: (40 / 320) * 100 = 12.5%\n  - Romance: (60 / 320) * 100 = 18.75%\n  - Non-fiction: (40 / 320) * 100 = 12.5%\n- Library B:\n  - Fiction: (150 / 450) * 100 = 33.33%\n  - Fantasy: (75 / 450) * 100 = 16.67%\n  - Horror: (60 / 450) * 100 = 13.33%\n  - Romance: (90 / 450) * 100 = 20%\n  - Non-fiction: (75 / 450) * 100 = 16.67%\n\n4. Difference in the overall ratio of checked-out Fiction and Non-fiction books between Library A and Library B:\n- Library A: 5:2\n- Library B: 2:1\nTo compare the ratios, we can convert them to a common denominator or express them as fractions and then subtract:\n- Library A: 5/2 = 2.5\n- Library B: 2/1 = 2\nDifference: 2.5 - 2 = 0.5 (or in ratio form, the difference is 1/2)\n\n5. Ratio of returned Fantasy, Horror, and Romance books combined to returned Fiction and Non-fiction books combined in both libraries:\n- Library A: (100 Fantasy + 60 Horror + 80 Romance) / (120 Fiction + 60 Non-fiction) = (240) / (180) = 240:180 = 4:3\n- Library B: (110 Fantasy + 70 Horror + 100 Romance) / (170 Fiction + 50 Non-fiction) = (280) / (220) = 280:220 = 7:5",
