    "id": 1224,
    "question": "A teacher has received funding from various sources for her school supplies. She has:\n\n1. $6 remaining from last year's budget, which needs to be converted from Euros (€) to US dollars ($) at a rate of 1€ = 1.2$.\n2. $50 from this year's school allocation.\n3. An additional $20 grant from a local charity.\n4. A $10 gift card for an online store where she plans to buy some of the items.\n\nShe purchases the following items:\n\n1. A package of textbooks that costs $45, but she has a 15% discount coupon for it. These textbooks have an 8% tax on them.\n2. A pack of notebooks for $18, with a 10% discount coupon and an additional 5% tax.\n3. A box of pens priced at $27, with a 5% discount due to a sale and a 6% tax rate.\n4. Art supplies worth $35, with no discounts available and a tax rate of 7%.\n5. A set of folders amounting to $15, and she has a $5-off voucher for this purchase. The folders have a tax rate of 4%.\n\nAfter converting last year's budget to US dollars, applying all the discounts, vouchers, gift cards, and adding relevant taxes, how much money will remain in her budget?\n\n### Answer:",
