    "id": 1225,
    "question": "A salt manufacturing company produced a total of 1000 tonnes of salt in January of a particular year. Starting from February, its production increased by varying percentages each month over the previous months until the end of the year. The percentage increments are as follows:\n\nFebruary: 5%\nMarch: 7%\nApril: 10%\nMay: 4%\nJune: 8%\nJuly: 5%\nAugust: 7%\nSeptember: 6%\nOctober: 12%\nNovember: 10%\nDecember: 8%\n\nFind its average monthly production for that year.\n\n### Answer:",
    "options": [
      "Option A",
      "Option B",
      "Option C",
      "Option D"
    ],
    "correct": 0,
    "explanation": "To find the average monthly production for the year, we first need to calculate the production for each month and then find the sum of all monthly productions. Finally, we divide the sum by 12 (the number of months in a year).\n\nLet's calculate the production for each month:\n\nJanuary: 1000 tonnes (given)\n\nFor the subsequent months, we will apply the percentage increase to the previous month's production.\n\nFebruary: 1000 + (5/100 * 1000) = 1000 + 50 = 1050 tonnes\nMarch: 1050 + (7/100 * 1050) = 1050 + 73.5 = 1123.5 tonnes\nApril: 1123.5 + (10/100 * 1123.5) = 1123.5 + 112.35 = 1235.85 tonnes\nMay: 1235.85 + (4/100 * 1235.85) = 1235.85 + 49.434 = 1285.284 tonnes\nJune: 1285.284 + (8/100 * 1285.284) = 1285.284 + 102.82272 = 1388.10672 tonnes\nJuly: 1388.10672 + (5/100 * 1388.10672) = 1388.10672 + 69.405336 = 1457.512056 tonnes\nAugust: 1457.512056 + (7/100 * 1457.512056) = 1457.512056 + 102.026044 = 1559.5381 tonnes\nSeptember: 1559.5381 + (6/100 * 1559.5381) = 1559.5381 + 93.572286 = 1653.110386 tonnes\nOctober: 1653.110386 + (12/100 * 1653.110386) = 1653.110386 + 198.37324632 = 1851.483632 tonnes\nNovember: 1851.483632 + (10/100 * 1851.483632) = 1851.483632 + 185.1483632 = 2036.631995 tonnes\nDecember: 2036.631995 + (8/100 * 2036.631995) = 2036.631995 + 162.9305596 = 2199.562555 tonnes\n\nNow, let's sum up all the monthly productions:\n\nSum = 1000 + 1050 + 1123.5 + 1235.85 + 1285.284 + 1388.10672 + 1457.512056 + 1559.5381 + 1653.110386 + 1851.483632 + 2036.631995 + 2199.562555\n\nSum = 17341.010444 tonnes\n\nFinally, we find the average monthly production by dividing the sum by 12:\n\nAverage monthly production = Sum / 12\nAverage monthly production = 17341.010444 / 12\nAverage monthly production ≈ 1445.084204 tonnes\n\nTherefore, the average monthly production for that year is approximately 1445.08 tonnes.",
