    "id": 1226,
    "question": "Natalia is participating in a week-long cycling competition. On Monday, she rode 40 kilometers and achieved a 5% bonus for her speed. On Tuesday, she rode 50 kilometers and earned a 3% bonus. On Wednesday, she rode 50% fewer kilometers than she did on Tuesday and gained a 7% bonus for her speed. On Thursday, she rode as many kilometers as the sum of the distances covered on Monday and Wednesday, and earned a 4% bonus for her speed.\n\nOn Friday, she increased her ride distance by 20% compared to the distance she covered on Thursday, and earned a 6% speed bonus. On Saturday, she covered 75% of the distance she covered on Friday but faced a challenging elevation gain, resulting in a 2% bonus. Finally, on Sunday she managed to ride as many kilometers as the difference between the distances she covered on Saturday and Wednesday, and due to an easier elevation, earned a 10% bonus for her speed.\n\nConsidering the base distances ridden each day, the bonuses earned for speed, and additional weekend rides with fluctuating elevation gains, how many kilometers did Natalia effectively ride in total during the week-long competition, including those earned from her speed bonuses?\n\n### Answer:",
    "options": [
      "Option A",
      "Option B",
      "Option C",
      "Option D"
    ],
    "correct": 0,
    "explanation": "Let's calculate the effective kilometers ridden each day, including the speed bonuses.\n\n**Monday:**\nBase distance: 40 km\nSpeed bonus: 5%\nEffective distance: 40 km + (5% of 40 km) = 40 km + (0.05 * 40 km) = 40 km + 2 km = 42 km\n\n**Tuesday:**\nBase distance: 50 km\nSpeed bonus: 3%\nEffective distance: 50 km + (3% of 50 km) = 50 km + (0.03 * 50 km) = 50 km + 1.5 km = 51.5 km\n\n**Wednesday:**\nBase distance: 50% fewer than Tuesday = 50 km / 2 = 25 km\nSpeed bonus: 7%\nEffective distance: 25 km + (7% of 25 km) = 25 km + (0.07 * 25 km) = 25 km + 1.75 km = 26.75 km\n\n**Thursday:**\nBase distance: Sum of Monday and Wednesday = 40 km + 25 km = 65 km\nSpeed bonus: 4%\nEffective distance: 65 km + (4% of 65 km) = 65 km + (0.04 * 65 km) = 65 km + 2.6 km = 67.6 km\n\n**Friday:**\nBase distance: 20% more than Thursday = 65 km + (20% of 65 km) = 65 km + (0.20 * 65 km) = 65 km + 13 km = 78 km\nSpeed bonus: 6%\nEffective distance: 78 km + (6% of 78 km) = 78 km + (0.06 * 78 km) = 78 km + 4.68 km = 82.68 km\n\n**Saturday:**\nBase distance: 75% of Friday = 75% of 78 km = 0.75 * 78 km = 58.5 km\nSpeed bonus: 2%\nEffective distance: 58.5 km + (2% of 58.5 km) = 58.5 km + (0.02 * 58.5 km) = 58.5 km + 1.17 km = 59.67 km\n\n**Sunday:**\nBase distance: Difference between Saturday and Wednesday = 58.5 km - 25 km = 33.5 km\nSpeed bonus: 10%\nEffective distance: 33.5 km + (10% of 33.5 km) = 33.5 km + (0.10 * 33.5 km) = 33.5 km + 3.35 km = 36.85 km\n\nNow, let's add up the effective distances for each day to get the total effective kilometers ridden during the week-long competition:\n\nTotal effective distance = 42 km (Monday) + 51.5 km (Tuesday) + 26.75 km (Wednesday) + 67.6 km (Thursday) + 82.68 km (Friday) + 59.67 km (Saturday) + 36.85 km (Sunday)\n\nTotal effective distance = 42 + 51.5 + 26.75 + 67.6 + 82.68 + 59.67 + 36.85 = 367.05 km\n\nNatalia effectively rode a total of 367.05 kilometers during the week-long competition, including the distances earned from her speed bonuses.",
