    "id": 1230,
    "question": "Vidya's mother's age is 5 years more than three times Vidya's present age. Her father's age is 7 years less than twice her mother's age. Vidya's grandmother is twice as old as Vidya's mother, while her grandfather is 3 years younger than her grandmother. In 5 years, Vidya's grandmother's age will be equal to the sum of Vidya's current age, her brother's age who is 2 years younger than her, their cousin's age who is half of Vidya's brother's age, and their aunt's age who is 1.5 times their mother's age. Find Vidya's age and the ages of all her family members.\n\n### Answer:",
