    "id": 1237,
    "question": "Consider three individuals, A, B, and C, whose salaries together amount to $3000. A spends 95% of their salary, B spends 85% of their salary, and C spends 80% of their salary. If the sum of A's and B's savings is equal to C's savings, and B's savings are twice A's savings, what are the salaries of A, B, and C?\n\n### Answer:",
