    "explanation": "Let's denote the salaries of A, B, and C as \\( S_A \\), \\( S_B \\), and \\( S_C \\) respectively. We are given that:\n\n\\[ S_A + S_B + S_C = 3000 \\]\n\nWe are also given that A spends 95% of their salary, B spends 85% of their salary, and C spends 80% of their salary. This means that A saves 5% of their salary, B saves 15% of their salary, and C saves 20% of their salary. \n\nSo, the savings of A, B, and C can be represented as:\n\n\\[ \\text{Savings}_A = 0.05S_A \\]\n\\[ \\text{Savings}_B = 0.15S_B \\]\n\\[ \\text{Savings}_C = 0.20S_C \\]\n\nWe are told that the sum of A's and B's savings is equal to C's savings:\n\n\\[ \\text{Savings}_A + \\text{Savings}_B = \\text{Savings}_C \\]\n\\[ 0.05S_A + 0.15S_B = 0.20S_C \\]\n\nAnd B's savings are twice A's savings:\n\n\\[ \\text{Savings}_B = 2 \\times \\text{Savings}_A \\]\n\\[ 0.15S_B = 2 \\times 0.05S_A \\]\n\\[ 0.15S_B = 0.10S_A \\]\n\nNow we have three equations:\n\n1. \\( S_A + S_B + S_C = 3000 \\)\n2. \\( 0.05S_A + 0.15S_B = 0.20S_C \\)\n3. \\( 0.15S_B = 0.10S_A \\)\n\nFrom equation 3, we can express \\( S_A \\) in terms of \\( S_B \\):\n\n\\[ S_A = \\frac{0.15}{0.10}S_B \\]\n\\[ S_A = 1.5S_B \\]\n\nNow we can substitute \\( S_A \\) in equation 1 with \\( 1.5S_B \\):\n\n\\[ 1.5S_B + S_B + S_C = 3000 \\]\n\\[ 2.5S_B + S_C = 3000 \\]\n\nAnd we can substitute \\( S_A \\) in equation 2 with \\( 1.5S_B \\):\n\n\\[ 0.05(1.5S_B) + 0.15S_B = 0.20S_C \\]\n\\[ 0.075S_B + 0.15S_B = 0.20S_C \\]\n\\[ 0.225S_B = 0.20S_C \\]\n\nNow we can express \\( S_C \\) in terms of \\( S_B \\):\n\n\\[ S_C = \\frac{0.225}{0.20}S_B \\]\n\\[ S_C = 1.125S_B \\]\n\nSubstitute \\( S_C \\) in the equation \\( 2.5S_B + S_C = 3000 \\) with \\( 1.125S_B \\):\n\n\\[ 2.5S_B + 1.125S_B = 3000 \\]\n\\[ 3.625S_B = 3000 \\]\n\\[ S_B = \\frac{3000}{3.625} \\]\n\\[ S_B = 827.59 \\]\n\nNow we can find \\( S_A \\) and \\( S_C \\):\n\n\\[ S_A = 1.5S_B \\]\n\\[ S_A = 1.5 \\times 827.59 \\]\n\\[ S_A = 1241.39 \\]\n\n\\[ S_C = 1.125S_B \\]\n\\[ S_C = 1.125 \\times 827.59 \\]\n\\[ S_C = 930.79 \\]\n\nSo the salaries of A, B, and C are approximately $1241.39, $827.59, and $930.79 respectively.",
