    "explanation": "Let's evaluate each expression using the given values for x, y, and z.\n\n1. \\( 4x^{-0.5} - 3y^{1/3} + 2z^{2/3} \\)\n\\( = 4(2)^{-0.5} - 3(3)^{1/3} + 2(4)^{2/3} \\)\n\\( = 4(1/\\sqrt{2}) - 3(\\sqrt[3]{3}) + 2(\\sqrt[3]{4^2}) \\)\n\\( = 4/\\sqrt{2} - 3\\sqrt[3]{3} + 2\\sqrt[3]{16} \\)\n\\( = 2\\sqrt{2} - 3\\sqrt[3]{3} + 2\\sqrt[3]{16} \\)\n\n2. \\( 6x^{-1} - 2y^{3/2} + 3z^{-2} \\)\n\\( = 6(2)^{-1} - 2(3)^{3/2} + 3(4)^{-2} \\)\n\\( = 6/2 - 2\\sqrt{3^3} + 3/4^2 \\)\n\\( = 3 - 2\\sqrt{27} + 3/16 \\)\n\\( = 3 - 2(3\\sqrt{3}) + 3/16 \\)\n\\( = 3 - 6\\sqrt{3} + 3/16 \\)\n\n3. \\( 2x^{3/4} - y^{-1/2} * z^{4/5} \\)\n\\( = 2(2)^{3/4} - (3)^{-1/2} * (4)^{4/5} \\)\n\\( = 2\\sqrt[4]{2^3} - 1/\\sqrt{3} * \\sqrt[5]{4^4} \\)\n\\( = 2\\sqrt[4]{8} - 1/\\sqrt{3} * \\sqrt[5]{256} \\)\n\\( = 2\\sqrt[4]{8} - 1/\\sqrt{3} * 4 \\)\n\n4. \\( x^{1/2} * y^{-4/3} - z^{-1/3} \\)\n\\( = (2)^{1/2} * (3)^{-4/3} - (4)^{-1/3} \\)\n\\( = \\sqrt{2} * 1/\\sqrt[3]{3^4} - 1/\\sqrt[3]{4} \\)\n\\( = \\sqrt{2} * 1/\\sqrt[3]{81} - 1/\\sqrt[3]{4} \\)\n\\( = \\sqrt{2} * 1/3\\sqrt[3]{3} - 1/\\sqrt[3]{4} \\)\n\\( = \\sqrt{2}/3\\sqrt[3]{3} - 1/\\sqrt[3]{4} \\)\n\nNow, let's calculate the numerical values for each expression:\n\n1. \\( 2\\sqrt{2} - 3\\sqrt[3]{3} + 2\\sqrt[3]{16} \\)\n\\( \\approx 2(1.414) - 3(1.442) + 2(2.519) \\)\n\\( \\approx 2.828 - 4.326 + 5.038 \\)\n\\( \\approx 3.540 \\)\n\n2. \\( 3 - 6\\sqrt{3} + 3/16 \\)\n\\( \\approx 3 - 6(1.732) + 0.1875 \\)\n\\( \\approx 3 - 10.392 + 0.1875 \\)\n\\( \\approx -7.2045 \\)\n\n3. \\( 2\\sqrt[4]{8} - 1/\\sqrt{3} * 4 \\)\n\\( \\approx 2(1.681) - 1/(1.732) * 4 \\)\n\\( \\approx 3.362 - 2.309 \\)\n\\( \\approx 1.053 \\)\n\n4. \\( \\sqrt{2}/3\\sqrt[3]{3} - 1/\\sqrt[3]{4} \\)\n\\( \\approx (1.414)/(3 * 1.442) - 1/(1.587) \\)\n\\( \\approx 0.327 - 0.630 \\)\n\\( \\approx -0.303 \\)\n\nThe expression with the greatest value is the first one, with an approximate value of 3.540.",
