    "id": 1259,
    "question": "Calculate the integral of (3x^2 - 5x + sqrt(2)) from x = 0.512 to x = 3.721.\n\n### Answer:",
    "options": [
      "Option A",
      "Option B",
      "Option C",
      "Option D"
    ],
    "correct": 0,
    "explanation": "To calculate the integral of the function \\(f(x) = 3x^2 - 5x + \\sqrt{2}\\) from \\(x = 0.512\\) to \\(x = 3.721\\), we first need to find the antiderivative of the function and then evaluate it at the upper and lower limits of integration.\n\nThe antiderivative of \\(f(x)\\) is:\n\\[\nF(x) = \\int (3x^2 - 5x + \\sqrt{2}) \\, dx = \\int 3x^2 \\, dx - \\int 5x \\, dx + \\int \\sqrt{2} \\, dx\n\\]\n\nIntegrating term by term, we get:\n\\[\nF(x) = \\frac{3}{3}x^3 - \\frac{5}{2}x^2 + \\sqrt{2}x + C\n\\]\n\\[\nF(x) = x^3 - \\frac{5}{2}x^2 + \\sqrt{2}x + C\n\\]\n\nSince we are evaluating a definite integral, we do not need to worry about the constant of integration \\(C\\). Now, we evaluate the antiderivative at the upper and lower limits:\n\n\\[\nF(3.721) = (3.721)^3 - \\frac{5}{2}(3.721)^2 + \\sqrt{2}(3.721)\n\\]\n\\[\nF(0.512) = (0.512)^3 - \\frac{5}{2}(0.512)^2 + \\sqrt{2}(0.512)\n\\]\n\nThe definite integral is then:\n\\[\n\\int_{0.512}^{3.721} (3x^2 - 5x + \\sqrt{2}) \\, dx = F(3.721) - F(0.512)\n\\]\n\nNow, let's calculate the values:\n\n\\[\nF(3.721) = (3.721)^3 - \\frac{5}{2}(3.721)^2 + \\sqrt{2}(3.721)\n\\]\n\\[\nF(3.721) = 51.421961 - \\frac{5}{2}(13.845841) + \\sqrt{2}(3.721)\n\\]\n\\[\nF(3.721) = 51.421961 - 34.6146025 + 5.260254\n\\]\n\\[\nF(3.721) = 51.421961 - 34.6146025 + 5.260254 \\approx 22.0676125\n\\]\n\n\\[\nF(0.512) = (0.512)^3 - \\frac{5}{2}(0.512)^2 + \\sqrt{2}(0.512)\n\\]\n\\[\nF(0.512) = 0.134217728 - \\frac{5}{2}(0.262144) + \\sqrt{2}(0.512)\n\\]\n\\[\nF(0.512) = 0.134217728 - 0.65536 + 0.7236067977\n\\]\n\\[\nF(0.512) = 0.134217728 - 0.65536 + 0.7236067977 \\approx 0.202464526\n\\]\n\nFinally, the definite integral is:\n\\[\n\\int_{0.512}^{3.721} (3x^2 - 5x + \\sqrt{2}) \\, dx = F(3.721) - F(0.512)\n\\]\n\\[\n\\int_{0.512}^{3.721} (3x^2 - 5x + \\sqrt{2}) \\, dx = 22.0676125 - 0.202464526\n\\]\n\\[\n\\int_{0.512}^{3.721} (3x^2 - 5x + \\sqrt{2}) \\, dx \\approx 21.865148\n\\]\n\nSo, the integral of \\(3x^2 - 5x + \\sqrt{2}\\) from \\(x = 0.512\\) to \\(x = 3.721\\) is approximately \\(21.865148\\).",
