    "question": "Feeling disheartened by their loss in their first game, Chuck and his teammates were determined to win their next match against the Yellow Team. Their match consisted of four quarters, and the teams earned points from field goals, three-pointers, free throws, and their opponents' personal fouls. Here's the breakdown of their scoring:\n\nFirst Quarter:\n- Chuck's Team: 9 field goals (2 points each) and 5 free throws (1 point each)\n- Yellow Team: 7 field goals (2 points each) and 4 three-pointers\n\nSecond Quarter:\n- Chuck's Team: 6 field goals (2 points each) and 3 three-pointers\n- Yellow Team: 5 field goals (2 points each), 2 three-pointers, and 3 free throws (1 point each)\n\nThird Quarter:\n- Chuck's Team: 4 field goals (2 points each), 2 three-pointers, and 6 free throws (1 point each)\n- Yellow Team: 6 field goals (2 points each) and 2 three-pointers\n\nFourth Quarter:\n- Chuck's Team: 8 field goals (2 points each) and 1 three-pointer\n- Yellow Team: 4 field goals (2 points each), 3 three-pointers, and 2 free throws (1 point each)\n\nAdditionally, Chuck's Team gained 3 points from technical fouls committed by the Yellow Team, while the Yellow Team gained 2 points from technical fouls committed by Chuck's Team.\n\nCalculate each team's total score and determine the size of Chuck's Team's lead.\n\n### Answer:",
