    "id": 1261,
    "question": "Jason went to the mall on Saturday to buy clothes and accessories for the upcoming summer season. He purchased the following items:\n\n1. Shorts for $14.28\n2. A jacket for $4.74\n3. A pair of shoes for $25.95\n4. A pack of socks for $6.80\n5. A set of two t-shirts for $18.36\n6. A hat for $12.50\n7. A swimming suit for $22.95\n8. A pair of sunglasses for $45.60\n9. A pack of three wristbands for $9.80\n\nIn order to promote seasonal shopping, the store offered a 20% discount on certain items (shorts, jacket, and hat) and a 10% discount on the other items.\n\nAdditionally, a sales tax of 8% was applied to the final discounted purchase price. Calculate the total amount Jason had to pay after considering the item-specific discounts and the sales tax applied to the total discounted price.\n\n### Answer:",
    "options": [
      "Option A",
      "Option B",
      "Option C",
      "Option D"
    ],
    "correct": 0,
    "explanation": "First, let's calculate the discounted price for each item:\n\n1. Shorts: $14.28 with a 20% discount\n   Discounted price = $14.28 - ($14.28 * 20%) = $14.28 - $2.856 = $11.424\n\n2. Jacket: $4.74 with a 20% discount\n   Discounted price = $4.74 - ($4.74 * 20%) = $4.74 - $0.948 = $3.792\n\n3. Shoes: $25.95 with a 10% discount\n   Discounted price = $25.95 - ($25.95 * 10%) = $25.95 - $2.595 = $23.355\n\n4. Socks: $6.80 with a 10% discount\n   Discounted price = $6.80 - ($6.80 * 10%) = $6.80 - $0.68 = $6.12\n\n5. T-shirts: $18.36 with a 10% discount\n   Discounted price = $18.36 - ($18.36 * 10%) = $18.36 - $1.836 = $16.524\n\n6. Hat: $12.50 with a 20% discount\n   Discounted price = $12.50 - ($12.50 * 20%) = $12.50 - $2.50 = $10.00\n\n7. Swimming suit: $22.95 with a 10% discount\n   Discounted price = $22.95 - ($22.95 * 10%) = $22.95 - $2.295 = $20.655\n\n8. Sunglasses: $45.60 with a 10% discount\n   Discounted price = $45.60 - ($45.60 * 10%) = $45.60 - $4.56 = $41.04\n\n9. Wristbands: $9.80 with a 10% discount\n   Discounted price = $9.80 - ($9.80 * 10%) = $9.80 - $0.98 = $8.82\n\nNow, let's add up all the discounted prices to get the total discounted purchase price:\n\nTotal discounted price = $11.424 + $3.792 + $23.355 + $6.12 + $16.524 + $10.00 + $20.655 + $41.04 + $8.82\nTotal discounted price = $141.73\n\nNow, we apply the sales tax of 8% to the total discounted price:\n\nSales tax = $141.73 * 8% = $141.73 * 0.08 = $11.3384\n\nFinally, we add the sales tax to the total discounted price to get the total amount Jason had to pay:\n\nTotal amount to pay = Total discounted price + Sales tax\nTotal amount to pay = $141.73 + $11.3384 = $153.0684\n\nRounded to two decimal places, Jason had to pay $153.07 after considering the item-specific discounts and the sales tax applied to the total discounted price.",
