    "question": "Olivia, Nigel, Beatrice, and Charles are traveling in Asia. They need to exchange their money to the local currency before they can enjoy the tourist attractions. The exchange rate is $1 USD to 110 local currency units (LCU).\n\nOlivia has $112, Nigel has $139, Beatrice has $167, and Charles has $191. After exchanging their money to LCU, they decide to visit three different tourist attractions.\n\nFor the first attraction, they buy four one-day passes costing 2,640 LCU each. For the second attraction, they buy four one-day passes costing 3,520 LCU each. Finally, for the third attraction, they buy four one-day passes with variable pricing as follows: 3,080 LCU for adults, 2,200 LCU for children, and 2,640 LCU for seniors (Age 60 and above).\n\nOlivia and Charles buy adult tickets, Nigel buys a child ticket, and Beatrice, being a senior citizen, buys a senior ticket for the third attraction.\n\nAdditionally, they spend 5,500 LCU on food and transportation during their trip. They share this cost equally among all four travelers.\n\nCalculate how much money in LCU each traveler has left after exchanging their money, purchasing tickets for all three attractions, and accounting for additional expenses on food and transportation.\n\n### Answer:",
